+    switch (paramArrayOfByte.length)
+    {
+    case 3: 
+    case 5: 
+    case 6: 
+    case 7: 
+    default: 
+      return 0L;
+    case 8: 
+      return paramArrayOfByte[0] << 56 & 0xFF00000000000000 | paramArrayOfByte[1] << 48 & 0xFF000000000000 | paramArrayOfByte[2] << 40 & 0xFF0000000000 | paramArrayOfByte[3] << 32 & 0xFF00000000 | paramArrayOfByte[4] << 24 & 0xFF000000 | paramArrayOfByte[5] << 16 & 0xFF0000 | paramArrayOfByte[6] << 8 & 0xFF00 | paramArrayOfByte[7] & 0xFF;
+    case 4: 
+      return b(paramArrayOfByte);
+    case 2: 
+      return c(paramArrayOfByte);
+    }
+    return paramArrayOfByte[0] & 0xFF;
+  }
+  
+  protected static byte[] a(int paramInt)
+  {
+    return new byte[] { (byte)((0xFF000000 & paramInt) >> 24), (byte)((0xFF0000 & paramInt) >> 16), (byte)((0xFF00 & paramInt) >> 8), (byte)(paramInt & 0xFF) };
+  }
+  
+  protected static byte[] a(short paramShort)
+  {
+    return new byte[] { (byte)((0xFF00 & paramShort) >> 8), (byte)(paramShort & 0xFF) };
+  }
+  
+  protected static int b(byte[] paramArrayOfByte)
+  {
+    return paramArrayOfByte[0] << 24 & 0xFF000000 | paramArrayOfByte[1] << 16 & 0xFF0000 | paramArrayOfByte[2] << 8 & 0xFF00 | paramArrayOfByte[3] & 0xFF;
+  }
+  
+  protected static int c(byte[] paramArrayOfByte)
+  {
+    return paramArrayOfByte[0] << 8 & 0xFF00 | paramArrayOfByte[1] & 0xFF;
+  }
